entries.description: A family of emus have been pictured walking across a suburban Aussie street, with many in awe over the unusual sight.

entries.title: Lemsip shortage due to 'a lack of planning' by government officials, pharmacy bosses say
entries.description: The Association of Independent Multiple Pharmacies has accused the Government of 'being in denial' over problems with the supply chain after reported shortages of cold and flu remedies.

entries.title: Cori Bush calls Byron Donalds a 'prop' for white supremacy after Speaker nomination
entries.description: Donalds was nominated as conservatives' alternative to embattled House GOP Leader Kevin McCarthy, whose quest for the gavel has been derailed so far.

entries.title: Pro-Brexit Reform UK party vows to contest every Conservative seat in next election
entries.description: Reform leader Richard Tice, pictured, who took over from Mr Farage in March 2021, gave a speech yesterday to re-launch the party.

entries.title: Drunk driver who 'killed' two Tennessee parents may have to pay child support under a new state law
entries.description: Patricke Conley, 42, was charged with homicide after he killed two parents and injured their three children in a crash on Christmas Day in Tennessee.

entries.title: Anti-strike laws to limit the power of militant unions could be unveiled 'in days'
entries.description: Ministers will unveil proposals to address the strikes crisis gripping the nation, the PM revealed, when asked how he would solve it without caving in to demands for inflation-level pay rises.

entries.title: Jill Biden to have procedure to have 'small lesion' removed after it was found above her right eye
entries.description: The lesion was discovered by Dr. Kevin O'Connor, Physician to the President, during a 'routine skin cancer screening.'

entries.title: Electric car sales overtake diesels for the first time in 2022
entries.description: Industry figures showed battery-powered cars made up 16.6 per cent of new registrations in 2022 while diesels fell below 10 per cent.

entries.title: MPs say a 'war effort' is needed to insulate Britain's draughty homes
entries.description: The Environmental Audit Committee recommended a 'national mobilisation' in order to improve energy efficiency standards in homes across the UK.

entries.title: Joy Behar rips 'conservatives' and 'heterosexual men' for supporting tackle football in schools
entries.description: Her comments come after Buffalo Bills player Damar Hamlin suffered a cardiac arrest on the field on Monday night and was left in a critical condition.

entries.title: Heavy metal band Iron Maiden celebrated in new set of stamps created by Royal Mail
entries.description: The eight stamps feature Iron Maiden performances and all current members of the band, including frontman Bruce Dickinson, who is also a qualified pilot.

entries.title: Texas man, 21, arrested after kidnapping Bumble date for five days and sexually assaulting her
entries.description: Zachary Kent Mills, 21, of Tomball, Texas  was arrested on December 30 and was charged with first-degree aggravated kidnapping. He allegedly held his Bumble date in his apartment for five days.

entries.title: Why have star-crossed lovers of Romeo and Juliet taken FIFTY YEARS to sue over sex scene?
entries.description: Plucked for stardom by director Franco Zeffirelli in his stunning adaptation of Romeo And Juliet, British actors Olivia Hussey and Leonard Whiting were hailed as the beautiful faces of a new generation
